A tragedy occurred on Sunday, when a truck with number plates SGM 715 XA loaded with a 20-foot container fell on a commercial bus stationed at Ilasamaja beneath the bridge, along Oshodi-Apapa Expressway, killing two persons with others injured in the process. According to an eyewitness, the accident occurred when the bus was discharging some of its passengers at the bus stop. “The impact of the fallen truck led to the immediate death of two yet-to-be-identified passengers; one male and one female,” the eyewitness narrated. General Manager, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency, LASEMA, Dr. Femi Oke-Osanyintolu, confirmed the incident. Oke-Osanyintolu said three other passengers, including the bus driver, were rescued with injuries and were immediately rushed to Isolo General Hospital. He added that another three passengers escaped unhurt. According to Oke-Osanyintolu, the bodies of the victims were taken to Isolo General Hospital mortuary. VANGUARD By Bose Adelaja The Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA) has said two persons died while three were injured when a 20-feet container fell on a commercial bus at Ilasamaja on the Oshodi-Badagry Expressway. LASEMA Director-General, Dr.+ Olufemi Oke-Osanyintolu, who confirmed the accident on Sunday in Lagos, said the dead… July 28, 2020 In "News" By Evelyn Usman Two persons lost their lives, yesterday, while several others were injured in an auto crash involving a Siena bus and a Lagos State Government campaign bus at Ile-Iwe bus stop, Idimu in Alimosho Local Government Area of Lagos. A report has it that the Siena bus loaded… April 3, 2020 In "Metro" By Olasunkanmi Akoni Tragedy struck in the early hours on Thursday, May 21, 2020, when a tanker suddenly rammed into a commercial bus and a car on the popular Otedola Bridge, along Lagos Ibadan-Expressway, killing an unidentified passenger, a female while others sustained injuries in the process. According to reports,… May 21, 2020 In "News"